# 1

1) enter

2) name of the host:
    hostname
    uname -n

3) arch of machine:
    uname -m
    date +'%d/%m/%Y %R'

5) print aliases, create alias newdate with previous output:
    alias
    alias newdate="date +'%d/%m/%Y %R'"

6) print env vars and describe some of them:
    env

    SHELL -- path to shell, command shell
    USER -- user that started current shell
    PATH -- search path for commands, left has more priority
    HOME -- users home directory
    LANG -- language that shell uses
    MAIL -- name of the file to check for incomig mail
    PS1 -- format of user input in shell, prompt string

7) change PS1, what changed?
    PS1='[\u@\h \W]\$ '
    PS1="\[\e[31;1m\]\u@\h\[\e[m\]:\[\e[1;34m\]\w\[\e[37;0m\]\$\[\e[37;0m\] "

8) change HOME var:
    ~ become full path

    all settings became default

9)
    which bash
    /usr/bin/bash


# 2


1) who am i
    whoami

2) all users that work with the system
    who

3) 3 users that logged last
    who -n 10

4) print user groups
    id -nG

5) 
    more /etc/passwd
    dozen40:x:1000:1000::/opt/.dozen40:/bin/bash

    1) login name
    2) optional encrypted password or x if in /etc/shadow
    3) user ID
    4) group ID
    5) comment to user account
    6) home dir
    7) command interpreter

6) -

7) - no permission

8) - no permission

